<HL>
   Business Brief -- American Express Co.:
   Accord Is Signed to Acquire
   Epsilon Data in Stock Swap
</HL>
<DATE>
05/25/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C16
</SO>
<CO>
   AXP EPSI
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
EARNINGS (ERN)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   American Express Co. said it signed an agreement to
acquire Epsilon Data Management Inc., a software and services
company, in a stock swap valued at about $64 million.
   American Express said Epsilon, of Burlington, Mass., will
be operated as part of its Direct Marketing and Travelers
Cheque Group, a unit of American Express Travel Related
Services Co.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Epsilon shareholders, who must approve the agreement, will
receive 0.655 share of newly issued American Express common
stock for each Epsilon share they own, subject to adjustment
if American Express stock falls below $28 or rises above $31
before the shareholders meet to ratify the deal.
   In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange,
American Express closed at $30 a share, up 25 cents.
   For the fiscal year ended May 31, 1989, Epsilon posted a
loss of $1.1 million, or 37 cents a share, on revenue of $51
million. For the quarter ended Feb. 28, the company earned
$552,000, or 19 cents a share, on revenue of $13 million.
</TEXT>
